accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research. This collection may require review before it is available for use. Please contact DCA for further details.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into three series: Annual reports; Patent files; and Unprocessed accessions.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office for Technology and Industry Collaboration was established in 2000 to handle intellectual property issues across all divisions of the university. The office is located on the Boston campus.

The Office for Technology Licensing and Industry Collaboration (OTL and IC) is responsible for facilitating the transfer of Tufts technology for public use and benefit. OTL and IC evaluates, obtains proprietary protection for, and assists in the distribution of technology for research and commercial purposes. OTL and IC is responsible for transferring technology for commercial development by identifying potential markets and negotiating license agreements with industry partners, be they large or start-up companies.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
